Interface IndexedCollectionProxy

IndexedListProxy, SetProxy
All Known Implementing Classes:
HashSetProxy, IndexedArrayListProxy
public interface IndexedCollectionProxy
extends Collection, Proxy

A collection of NamedProxy objects.

This interface represents a collection of named elements that can be accessed both through the standard Collection interface, and through more specialised methods enabling quick access based on names. It also includes some more sophisticated exception handling.

Implementations of this interface can be used like a collection with the restriction that they only accept elements of type NamedProxy. Furthermore, these elements will be indexed using their names as obtained by the NamedProxy.getName() method. Implementations must ensure that there cannot be two different elements with the same in a collection at the same time, where the equals() method is used to determine whether two elements are to be considered as equal.

Author:
Robi Malik

init

public void init(Collection elist,
                 ProxyFactory factory)
          throws ModelException
Initialise the collection with a set of JAXB elements. This method creates proxies for all elements of the given collection and adds them to this collection. This method is intended for internal use during marshalling only.

Parameters:
elist - List of elements to be added, each element should be of type ElementType.
factory - A factory used to create ElementProxy objects from the members of elist.
Throws:
DuplicateNameException - to indicate that it was attempted to create two elements with the same name in this collection.
ModelException - to indicate that proxy creation has failed for one of the elements.

insert

public NamedProxy insert(NamedProxy proxy)
                  throws ModelException
Tries to add an element to this collection. This method first checks whether the collection already contains a different item with the same name, and fails if this is the case. The equals() method is used to check whether elements are equal.

Parameters:
proxy - The item to be added.
Returns:
The item that is now contained in the collection. This may be the given item or another one that is equal and was there before.
Throws:
DuplicateNameException - to indicate that the collection already has a different item with the same name.
ModelException - to indicate that the element cannot be added because of some reason depending on the specific type of collection and element.
